		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message30707891">This is an awfully quick response but nevertheless, Jojo's Bizarre Adventure(2012) is an adaptation of the first 2 parts of the manga and here is where my problems lie: the first part is incredibly flawed with a bland main character in Jonathon, a cliche but charismatic villain in Dio, a struggle to properly balance the drama, action and comedy unlike the rest of the series and the other characters hardly get any substantial screen time. Luckily this arc only lasts for a short period of time. <br />
<br />
Battle Tendency however fixes these problems, except for the latter, but this serves as both a pro and a con for the series. The reason being is that Joseph Joestar is one of the best characters in the Jojo series: charismatic, unpredictable, chivalrous, clever and more. He's the embodiment of everything that Jojo represents and pretty much carries the whole arc. This still isn't enough for me to turn a blind eye as to how underutilized other good characters like Lisa Lisa and Caesar were though..I also really like how Joseph's habits of trickery do add to the more tactical approach of the fights in comparison to Phantom Blood. The parallels between Joseph and Caesar and Joseph and Wham are always fun to watch. To see the actual adventure side of the Jojo series be explored along with its creative use of the ripples make this arc a stand-out epic before the stands are introduced. Yes it has its cliches, lack of logic sometimes, unbelievable explanations etc. but its fun, a whole lot of fun.<br />
<br />
The low budget can be a bit jarring sometimes considering how a lot of Joseph's characterisation comes from his actions, gestures, body language..so you can argue that the animation doesn't properly convey these. At least it seems like that won't be a problem for the other parts (hopefully we get adaptations of all the other parts!).</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
