		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message31020997"><!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>Po_and_Dong said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br>I thought it was alright. I think if you strip away the iconic fabulousness though you are left with a very typical action show.<!--quote--></div><br />
<div class="spoiler"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.nextSibling.nextSibling.style.display='block';this.style.display='none';" value="Show spoiler"> <span class="spoiler_content" style="display:none"><input type="button" class="button" onClick="this.parentNode.style.display='none';this.parentNode.parentNode.childNodes[0].style.display='block';" value="Hide spoiler"><br><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/i2yFvgw.jpg" /><!--spoiler--></span></div><br />
<br />
Okay, okay, I kid. But seriously, if you honestly think that JoJo's Bizarre Adventure falls into the same pitfalls as every other battle shonen then you clearly have no understanding of how other battle shonen worked - or, more often, did not work - in the first place.<br />
<br />
To paraphrase my spotlight post for Battle Tendency over in CnC:<br />
<br />
&quot;In my opinion, JoJo's Bizarre Adventure is what every battle shonen should strive to be: as fun as possible. It constantly strives to be as quirky and fun as conceivably possible. The excellent art style, along with Araki Hirohiko's wonderfully insane fashion sense (increasingly insane with each arc), makes JJBA visually appealing as all hell, alongside the tongue-in-cheek music references, and the sheer lunacy of a lot of the events in the series, JJBA is a guaranteed thrill ride. But what really sets it apart are the fights. The fights in JJBA are a cut above the rest of the shonen crop and then some, relying, rather than on having the supporting cast hold out against the Big Bad until the big hero gets there, or upping the ante through a series of increasingly irrational and convoluted powerups, the fights of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure rely on one main feature: trickery. Every battle in JJBA is as much a battle of wits as it is a battle of physical strength. The fights are all set up, or manipulated to be, based on how one can use one's power rather than how much power there is. What I really love is, no matter what power someone gets stuck with, they will always find a way to get the best out of it.&quot;</div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by Lindle, 06-09-14, 8:13 PM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://i.imgur.com/Y1FB912.png" /><br />
<span style="font-size: 150%;"><!--link--><a href="http://theotaku2anime.wordpress.com/2014/04/28/joe-the-lion-crackpot-jojolion-theory-time/#more-1192" rel="nofollow">Latest Blog: Joe The Lion - Crackpot JoJolion Theory Time!</a></div></td>
